# Next.js v16.1.6 - Official Rules

> Source: https://nextjs.org/docs (vercel/next.js v16.1.5)
> Last fetched: 2026-02-05

## ABSOLUTE PROHIBITIONS (ZERO TOLERANCE)

### Universal
- NO placeholders: `TODO`, `FIXME`, `XXX`, `HACK`, `...`, `implement later`
- NO mock data in production code
- NO hardcoded secrets, API keys, passwords
- NO `console.log` statements in production
- NO empty catch blocks
- NO magic numbers without constants

### TypeScript/JavaScript
- NO `any` type
- NO `@ts-ignore` or `@ts-expect-error`
- NO `// eslint-disable`
- NO `as any` type assertions
- NO `!` non-null assertion without justification
- NO `eval()` or `Function()` constructor

### Next.js Specific
- NO `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` without sanitization
- NO inline styles (`style={{...}}`) - use Tailwind CSS
- NO hardcoded URLs/domains in metadata or sitemap
- NO missing `key` prop in lists
- NO `useEffect` with missing dependencies
- NO `getServerSideProps` or `getStaticProps` in App Router (use Server Components)
- NO client-side data fetching for initial page data (use Server Components)

## REQUIRED Patterns

### App Router Architecture

```tsx
// Server Component (default) - no 'use client' directive
export default async function Page() {
  const data = await fetchData() // Direct async/await
  return <div>{data.title}</div>
}

// Client Component - only when needed
'use client'
export function InteractiveComponent() {
  const [state, setState] = useState()
  return <button onClick={() => setState(!state)}>Toggle</button>
}
```

### Data Fetching with Caching

```tsx
// Static data (cached until revalidation)
const staticData = await fetch('https://...', { cache: 'force-cache' })

// Dynamic data (no cache)
const dynamicData = await fetch('https://...', { cache: 'no-store' })

// Time-based revalidation
const revalidatedData = await fetch('https://...', {
  next: { revalidate: 60 } // Revalidate every 60 seconds
})
```

### Server Actions

```tsx
// actions.ts
'use server'

import { revalidatePath } from 'next/cache'
import { redirect } from 'next/navigation'

export async function createItem(formData: FormData) {
  const title = formData.get('title') as string
  
  // Validate with Zod
  const parsed = schema.safeParse({ title })
  if (!parsed.success) {
    return { error: parsed.error.flatten() }
  }
  
  await db.item.create({ data: parsed.data })
  
  revalidatePath('/items')
  redirect('/items')
}
```

### Forms with Server Actions

```tsx
import Form from 'next/form'
import { createItem } from '@/actions'

export default function Page() {
  return (
    <Form action={createItem}>
      <input name="title" required />
      <button type="submit">Create</button>
    </Form>
  )
}
```

### Cache Tags and Revalidation

```tsx
import { cacheTag, updateTag } from 'next/cache'

// Tag data in Server Component
export async function getCart() {
  'use cache'
  cacheTag('cart')
  return await fetchCart()
}

// Revalidate in Server Action
export async function updateCart(itemId: string) {
  'use server'
  await updateCartItem(itemId)
  updateTag('cart')
}
```

## FORBIDDEN Patterns

### Wrong: Using getServerSideProps in App Router
```tsx
// WRONG - Pages Router pattern
export async function getServerSideProps() {
  const data = await fetchData()
  return { props: { data } }
}
```

### Wrong: Client-side fetching for initial data
```tsx
// WRONG
'use client'
export function Page() {
  const [data, setData] = useState(null)
  useEffect(() => {
    fetch('/api/data').then(r => r.json()).then(setData)
  }, [])
  return <div>{data?.title}</div>
}
```

### Correct: Server Component with direct fetch
```tsx
// CORRECT
export default async function Page() {
  const data = await fetch('https://api.example.com/data')
  return <div>{data.title}</div>
}
```

## Image Optimization

```tsx
import Image from 'next/image'

// CORRECT
<Image
  src="/photo.jpg"
  alt="Description"
  width={800}
  height={600}
  priority // For above-the-fold images
/>

// WRONG
<img src="/photo.jpg" alt="Description" />
```

## Metadata Configuration

```tsx
// app/layout.tsx
import type { Metadata } from 'next'

export const metadata: Metadata = {
  title: {
    default: 'EviDive',
    template: '%s | EviDive'
  },
  description: 'Dive center booking platform',
  openGraph: {
    type: 'website',
    locale: 'fr_FR',
  },
}
```

## Route Protection with Middleware

```tsx
// middleware.ts
import { NextResponse } from 'next/server'
import type { NextRequest } from 'next/server'

export function middleware(request: NextRequest) {
  // Check auth, locale, etc.
  return NextResponse.next()
}

export const config = {
  matcher: ['/((?!api|_next/static|_next/image|favicon.ico).*)'],
}
```

## Enforcement

This rule file has `alwaysApply: true`. Violations will be:
1. Flagged immediately
2. Blocked from generation
3. Required to be fixed before proceeding
